<p><font style="font-weight: bold;" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3">Immersion 
improved through:</font><font style="font-weight: bold;" size="+3"> </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3"><br></font><font size="+3"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3">&#8226; matching input from at least two sensors</font><font size="+3"> </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3"><br> 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#8226; high refresh rate <font size="+2">(forgo photorealistic verisimilitude if needed</font> </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3"><a href="wireframe.png"><img style="border: 0px solid ; width: 11px; height: 11px;" src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" alt="The linked image shows a wireframe face"></a><font size="+2"> )</font></font><br>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3"> 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#8226; small delays after user actions <font size="+2">(&lt; 100 msec)</font></font><font size="+2"> 
</font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3"><br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#8226; 
at least monoscopic view with motion parallax</font><font size="+3"> </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+2">(but added stereoscopy is better)</font><font size="+3"> </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+3"><br> 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#8226; three-dimensional sound</font> </p>
